snippet.textDisplay:
I concede your point about the conflict between “real rap” and “mumble rap”. I’m just worried the further we stray away from the core of what makes rap, rap, the more over saturated and diluted the genre becomes. Happened with rock; country, blues, etc.

There will always be “lyrical rappers”, I just think the lines get so weirdly blurred at times on what is to be considered “rap”. When lyrics clearly take a backseat to repetitive auto-tuned melodies and clich’e rap tropes.
